description:
&lt;p&gt;Workplace Health and Wellbeing would like to welcome an Occupational Health Technician to join their clinical team at Rouen Road. The post holder will undertake a range of health screening activities as well as administrative tasks in planning Health &amp; Wellbeing events. The post holder will deliver services to both NHS and non-NHS customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As post holder, you will assist the delivery of Occupational Health services both to the Trust and other external contracts under the supervision of a qualified occupational health nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will undertake a variety of clinical and administrative tasks. The clinical tasks will include a health screening activities (eg Spirometry, audiometry, vision screening, height, weight, blood pressure, blood taking etc). The administrative tasks will involve activities such as entering results into our OH software system, planning Health &amp; Wellbeing events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to drive throughout Norfolk and Suffolk providing clinic and site visits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be a requirement to work evenings on occasions and also some early mornings according to contract demands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time:&lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date:&lt;/strong&gt; 27th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 26th October 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Karen Carpenter - Senior Occupational Health Nurse Advisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01603 287035&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: karen.carpenter@nnuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
